----------------
As requested in a comment, I&#39;ll try to explain the regex: `(/[^/]*){2}/([^/]*)`

![Regular expression visualization](https://www.debuggex.com/i/2sAKhlPpasMkBR31.png)

* `/[^/]*` is a `/` followed by `[^/]*` (any number of characters that are not a `/`),
* `(/[^/]*)` groups the previous expression in a single entity. This is the `1`st group of the expression,
* `(/[^/]*){2}` means that the group must match extactly `{2}` times,
* `[^/]*` is again any number of characters that are not a `/`,
* `([^/]*)` groups the previos expression in a single entity. This is the `2`nd group of the expression.

This way you have only to get the substring that matches the 2nd group: `return m.group(2);`

Image courtesy by [Debuggex](https://www.debuggex.com/r/2sAKhlPpasMkBR31)

