The `assertEquals` method checks whether two objects are equal using the [Object.equals](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Object.html#equals-java.lang.Object-) method. This method is often overwritten in a class to check whether two instances of the class are equal, but if it&#39;s not overwritten, this method will just check whether the objects are the same instance.

Since the libgdx class [Texture](https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/blob/master/gdx/src/com/badlogic/gdx/graphics/Texture.java) doesn&#39;t overwrite the equals method your test asserts that both objects are the same instance, but not that they contain the same pixel data.

A solution would be to implement a new method `areTexturesEqual(Texture t1, Texture t2)` that checks whether the textures are equal:

```
@Test
