Basically **you can&#39;t**: once the `Configuration` is initialized, the `ConfigurationSource` is no longer available.

You can however loop through the runtime components and retrieve the properties you want. For example if you want to log all `filePattern` properties of the configured `RollingFileAppender`s, you can use:

```lang-java
final LoggerContext ctx = LogManager.getContext(false);
if (ctx instanceof org.apache.logging.log4j.core.LoggerContext) {
    final Configuration config = ((org.apache.logging.log4j.core.LoggerContext) ctx)
            .getConfiguration();
    final LoggerConfig rootLogger = config.getRootLogger();
    for (final Appender appender : rootLogger.getAppenders().values()) {
        if (appender instanceof RollingFileAppender) {
            final RollingFileAppender rfa = (RollingFileAppender) appender;
            logger.info(&quot;Found appender with name {} and file pattern {}.&quot;, rfa.getName(),
                    rfa.getFilePattern());
        }
    }
}
```

However there is no hard rule on where to find the property or whether it is even available in runtime: e.g. many `Appender` properties are stored in their managers. To provide another example: the `append` property of file appenders is only available through reflection on the `OutputStream` underlying the appender.

